8-03 02:10:55',0),(12232,1,2,'form_observations_set_observation_date_to','Set observation date to','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12233,1,2,'form_observations_set_image_dates_to','Set image dates to','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12234,1,2,'form_observations_image_too_big','This image is too large. Images must be less than [:max]Mb in file size.','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12235,1,2,'list_countries_title','Countries with Observations','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12236,2,2,'news_content','August 3, 2015. <u>MycoBank Links</u>\n\nNames and Observations now include links to a MycoBank search for the named taxon. If Mycobank has an official translation in your MO Language, the search will take you to that translation.\nWhy not also Index Fungorum? Unfortunately Index Fungorum does not currently provide for this kind of search.\n\n\nJuly 3, 2015. <u>New UI, Rails 4.0 upgrade</u>\n\nHi All,\n\nIf you are reading this, then we have finally gotten out a new release for Mushroom Observer that we\'ve been working on for months.\n\nThe original goal of this release was to update our infrastructure to something more recent (Rails 4.0 for those who care about such things).  This upgrade was spearheaded by Joe Cohen.  However, some of these infrastructure changes required major changes to the way we handle our user interface (UI).  Fortunately, Ray Suelzer stepped forward and undertook the daunting task of bringing the Mushroom Observer UI into the current decade.  This is a huge change that has literally affected every interface in the system.  Along the way some significant UI changes were made which we think overall will improve the experience of using the site for everyone.\n\nThat being said, the underlying data model, voting and naming system, etc. has not changed.  We hope to go after some of these known issues soon, but our first goal has had to be bringing the underlying systems up to date.  While this particular upgrade is significant, it is, unfortunately, not the end of the road for needed infrastructure upgrades. However, we hope that this new release has laid the groundwork for making those additional updates much easier.\n\nThat being said, here\'s a list of the biggest changes that have happened to the Mushroom Observer interface:\n\n<b>New Layout</b> - The most obvious change that you will see is that there is a new layout. The primary goals of the new layout were to make the website friendly for mobile devices, and to create a cleaner and simpler user experience. We tried to keep the feel of the site largely the same, but we did make some significant changes along the way. Here are the changes in the layout, why we made them, and how they might impact you.\n\n<ol><li><p><b>Removed \"matrix\" style boxes</b>. This is the most significant change to the layout. The old layout used HTML tables to render content into different squares. While this worked very well when the site was initially coded, the rise of mobile phones and smaller devices required us to abandon having a fixed number of columns per row. When viewing the site on a smaller screen the content will automatically switch to a smaller number of columns so you can view content just as easily on a phone as on a computer. This change required us to drop the existing preference of defining how many columns and rows you would like to show on each page, since we want to automatically display the information in a format that reasonably fits your screen. Instead, you can now set how many results you would like to display on each page. The framework we are working with supports three screen resolutions and we have tuned the site to work with the most standard screen sizes given our content.  As a result we could not find an easy way to support the small number of users who have chosen to use an increased number of columns presumably for very large screens.  If this has a big effect on your workflow, please let us know and we\'ll see if we can work out something that addresses your needs.</p></li><li><p><b>Left Navigation Bar Changes</b> -<ol><li>We looked at the analytics of which links people were using most frequently and reordered the navigation bar to reflect this usage. This should ultimately provide for an easier experience for everyone, but there may be a bit of transition pain for those who have become used to the old layout. We also added a link to \"Your Lists.\"</li><li>We reduced the number of items in the sidebar by putting the different language options in a dropdown, which will make it easier for users to find the more frequently used links more quickly.</li><li>On mobile devices the Navigation Bar will now slide out from the side with a \"hamburger\" button. This gives users the experience they expect when viewing a website on their phone.</li><li>Most of the items related to your account have moved to the top navigation bar.</li></ol></p></li><li><p><b>Top Navigation Bar</b> - The search bar remains at the top, but we have added some special icons for the user to the far right.<ol><li>If you are not logged in, you will see two buttons \"Create an Account\" or \"Login\".</li><li>If you are logged in you will see a few new icons.<ol><li>The \"cog\" or \"gear\" will take you to the user preference page.</li><li>The \"inbox\" will take you to see comments for you.</li><li>The \"horn\" will take you to see all of the different observations or other items that you are following.</li><li>The \"door\" will sign you out.</li><li>If you click on your username, you will see a dropdown of more actions associated with your account. Such as showing your observations, species lists, and your summary.</li></ol></li></ol></p></li></ol>\n\n<b>Images</b> - We spent time thinking about how we deal with images on the website. We decided that some of the current options should be replaced with a more modern experience. Here is a list of changes that relate to images.<ol><li><p><b>Theater View</b> - When you hover over any image on the site with your mouse, you will see an \"expand\" icon appear in the top right of the image. Clicking this will open the image in full-screen. You can close the view by pressing escape, clicking the \"X\" button in the top right, or clicking in the grey area outside of the image. If you want to view or download the original image, simply click on the image in the full-screen.</p></li><li><p><b>Show Image Page</b> - The show image page previously allowed a user to set the default image size to anything from \"small\" to \"huge\". The reality of this feature was that setting the default size to anything larger than \"medium\" caused the image to go off of the screen and degraded the experience of the page. To that end, the show image page will default to showing the image to be as large as will fit on your screen. If you want to see the image even larger, you can click the \"theater\" button and if you want to see the original image size, which with today’s cameras will not fit on even the largest of screens, you can click the image after it appears in full-screen view. In most modern browsers this will allow you to zoom in to full resolution.</p></li><li><p><b>Images on show observation page</b> - Discussed more in the changes to the \"show observation\" page below.</p></li></ol>\n\n<b>Changes to Show Observation Pages</b> - The most commonly viewed page on MO is the show observation page. As such, we took some time reworking how this page is laid out and attempted to simplify the design to make an observation more easily digestible at first glance.<ol><li><p><b>Images front and center</b> - The most useful information in an observation is often the images. As such we added an image carousel that will display the images at the top of the page and allow a user to scroll back and forth through the images. We also wanted to reduce the clutter on the page, but still allow users to access important information about images such as notes and (where available) the original filename. These data are now hidden, but you can see them by simply placing your mouse over one of the images.</p></li><li><p><b>Moved information about the \"name\" of the observation to its own box</b> - Previously this information was found up top in the title, we felt that this information was too useful to hide up there so it was placed in its own box above the \"map\".</p></li><li><p><b>Map</b> - The map now resizes to fit the screen it is being viewed on.</p></li><li><p><b>Species Lists</b> - Species lists associated with the observation are now on the right.</p></li><li><p><b>Proposed Names</b> - Proposed names and namings were given more space to breathe and are displayed directly under the images.</p></li><li><p><b>Comments</b> - The layout for how comments look was updated to be a cleaner and are now shown directly at the bottom.<p></li></ol>\n\n<b>Dismissible Top Banner Messages</b> - We wanted to retain a way to notify users of important updates and changes across the top of the page in a message banner, but to allow users to hide the banner after they have read the message. By clicking the \"x\" button on the top banner, it will be hidden for a month, or until something else important comes up.\n\n<b>Tweaks to create observation page</b> - We wanted users to be able to quickly add observations from their phones and clean up the create observations page. The updated create observation page is mobile friendly and a user can upload images directly from their phone and create an observation.\n\n<b>And much more...</b> - Many other more subtle changes and tweaks were made to the site that we hope improve the overall experience on Mushroom Observer.  We think everyone will get something out of the new changes and we have tested things pretty throughly, but we will not be surprised if we missed somethings.  Please let us know if you see something strange or broken or if there are further user interface changes that you would like to see.\n\nWe hope you enjoy the new interface!\n\nThe Mushroom Observer Development Team','2015-11-07 22:55:42',0),(12237,2,2,'show_name_on_mycoportal','on MyCoPortal','2015-11-07 22:55:42',0),(12238,1,2,'add_specimen_herbarium_label_help','(initial determination and unique herbarium id)','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12239,1,2,'pivotal_label_descriptions','descriptions','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12240,1,2,'pivotal_label_js','javascript','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12241,1,2,'pivotal_label_mobile','mobile','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12242,1,2,'pivotal_label_preferences','prefs','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12243,1,2,'pivotal_label_rss','rss','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12244,1,2,'pivotal_label_specimens','specimens','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12245,1,2,'pivotal_label_tests','tests','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12246,1,2,'pivotal_label_textile','textile','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12247,1,2,'pivotal_label_users','users','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12248,1,2,'api_bad_herbarium_parameter_value','Invalid or unknown herbarium, \"[val]\", accept numerical id, code or name.','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12249,1,2,'api_can_only_use_this_field_if_has_specimen','The parameter, \"[field]\", can only be used if the observation has a specimen.','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12250,1,2,'api_can_only_use_one_of_these_fields','Please only use one of these parameters: [fields].','2015-08-03 02:10:55',0),(12251,1,2,'image_set_default','Set as default thumbnail','2015-11-07 22:55:42',0),(12252,1,2,'prefs_layout_count','List page items','2015-11-07 22:55:42',0),(12253,1,2,'prefs_view_owner_id','View Observer identification of Observations?','2015-11-07 22:55:42',0),(12254,1,2,'show_name_on_mycobank','on MycoBank','2015-11-07 22:55:42',0),(12255,1,2,'show_observation_site_id','Site ID','2015-11-07 22:55:42',0),(12256,1,2,'show_observation_owner_id','Observer ID','2015-11-07 22:55:42',0),(12257,1,2,'view_owner_id_help','When checked, causes Observations to display Observer ID (the observer\'s choice of name for the taxon), if it is different from consensus a